result.execSummary:
The defendant Clyde E White was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Clyde E White is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Clyde E White was found guilty of Battery, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Clyde E White in court with attorney Valeria Lenise Taylor.  Defendant Clyde E White in custody.  Michael Lonski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  

As to Count 2:
The Court sentenced the defendant to 6 MONTHS in the House of Corrections with 237 days credit.  TIME SERVED.

Court ordered the defendant provide a DNA sample.

Court ordered the defendant pay all of the following by the end of supervision in Case# 14CF915.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment:
Restitution in the amount of $1,700.93 payable to Joshua W; 
All court costs, fees, and surcharges (including DNA); 
All applicable fees of supervision.
-  Cash bail on deposit be applied.
-  Court ordered that all court costs, fines, surcharges and/or restitution be paid through collection by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision. DOC shall collect those sums in Case# 14CF915.

Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm. 
Court advised defendant of his right to seek postconviction relief.
Court advised defendant that he may not vote until his civil rights have been restored.

Defendant Clyde E White in court with attorney Valeria Lenise Taylor.  Defendant Clyde E White in custody.  Thomas L. Potter for Michael Lonski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Pursuant to plea negotiations, Counts 1 and 3 are dismissed.  As to Count 2:
  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  
Case is adjourned for sentencing in Branch 22.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for November 14, 2014 at 08:30 am.
